This paper discusses the application of Software Defined Networking (SDN) and Network Functions Virtualization (NFV) in critical infrastructure networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the requirements of industrial communications, such as system modularity and secure network access, which could be classified under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the design of the VirtuWind architecture, which involves the integration of various functional components, such as Quality of Service (QoS) guarantees and multi-tenant capability, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY), software engineering (cs.SE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
